"```sql\nSELECT \n  (COUNT(*) FILTER (WHERE circuits.country = 'Germany')::float / COUNT(*)) * 100 AS percentage\nFROM \n  races\nJOIN \n  circuits ON races.circuitId = circuits.circuitId\nWHERE \n  races.name = 'European Grand Prix';\n```\nThis SQL query calculates the percentage of European Grand Prix races that were hosted in Germany by joining the `races` and `circuits` tables and filtering the results based on the race name and circuit country."